---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NavBar from '../components/NavBar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = 'July 1, 2026';
---

<Layout title="Privacy policy — Free Format Convert" description="How Free Format Convert handles (and mostly doesn't handle) your data.">
	<NavBar />
	<main>
		<PageHeader title="Privacy policy" subtitle={`Effective ${EFFECTIVE_DATE}`} />
		<section class="privacy-body">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="prose">
					<p>
						Free Format Convert is built so that there's as little to say in a privacy policy as possible. Here's exactly what
						happens — and doesn't happen — to your data.
					</p>

					<h2>Your files</h2>
					<p>
						<strong>We never receive your files.</strong> Every conversion runs locally in your browser using the Canvas
						API and WebAssembly (ffmpeg.wasm). Your file is read from disk into browser memory, converted, and offered
						back to you as a download — it never travels over the network to any server we control. There is no upload
						step in this product.
					</p>

					<h2>What we do load from the network</h2>
					<p>
						For video and audio conversions, your browser downloads a conversion engine (an open-source WebAssembly
						build of ffmpeg, a few dozen megabytes) from a public CDN the first time you need it in a session. That
						request contains no information about your file — it's just fetching program code, the same way loading
						any other script on this page works. The CDN operator may log standard request metadata (like any web
						request), but it never sees your file.
					</p>

					<h2>Analytics and cookies</h2>
					<p>
						Free Format Convert does not use tracking cookies and does not run third-party analytics that profile individual
						visitors. Our hosting provider may keep standard, aggregate server access logs (e.g. request counts, response
						times) for operating the site reliably — the same baseline logging any web host performs.
					</p>

					<h2>Local storage</h2>
					<p>
						We store one small preference in your browser's local storage: your light/dark theme choice. It never
						leaves your device and contains no personal information.
					</p>

					<h2>Third parties</h2>
					<p>
						Because files are never uploaded, there's no third party that ever receives your file content, converted
						output, or filenames. The only outbound request the Service makes is the one-time engine download described
						above.
					</p>

					<h2>Children's privacy</h2>
					<p>
						The Service does not knowingly collect personal information from anyone, including children, because it
						does not collect file content or account data from any user.
					</p>

					<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
					<p>
						If this policy changes, we'll update the effective date above. Meaningful changes to how the Service
						handles data will be reflected here first.
					</p>

					<h2>Contact</h2>
					<p>
						Questions about this policy? Reach out via our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
	.privacy-body {
		padding-bottom: var(--space-5xl);
	}
</style>
